;; Hi folks.
;; 
;; Here is version 3.03 of face-lock, a package that lets you use any mixture
;; of colours, colors, bold, italics, underline etc. for font-lock-mode.
;; 
;; By default, colour and color displays will get colours and colors,
;; grayshade displays get suitable grayshades and fonts, and monochrome
;; displays get fonts.  The package works out what sort of display you are
;; using, and uses the appropriate display style.  You can even display
;; things in bold, italic, underline hot pink if you so wish.  It probably
;; works with Lucid.
;; 
;; Some major differences over the previous version released to
;; gnu.emacs.sources:
;; 
;; - face-lock will not over-ride face X resources.  This means that
;;   you can selectively set certain X resources for font-lock faces, as an
;;   alternative to `setq'ing in your ~/.emacs.
;; - the face attribute structure is much simplified; but you can now specify
;;   the background attribute as well.
;; - some face attributes have changed (especially the non-colour ones).
;; - command and function names have changed (a preliminary to merging with
;;   font-lock).
;; 
;; Note that you can pick it up from the Emacs Lisp Archive.  See the comment
;; header.
;; 
;; Enjoy.  Simon.
